h4. Summary

Currently, the Header Highlight Background Color is also applied on the logo. This is causing cosmetic issues when hovering the mouse over the logo:
 - Using a transparent logo, having the logo text and the Header Highlight Background Color in the same color, the logo text disappears.
 - Using a non-transparent logo, the Header Highlight Background Color is applied around the logo (showing a frame) which looks deforming.

h4. Notes

It would be nice if the Header Highlight Background Color wouldn't be applied on the logo, as the logo is something static that should not be manipulated or highlighted by the UI.

h4. Workaround

Apply the following script to the announcement banner. This script prevents the section in which the logo resides from having the Header Highlight Background Color being applied:
{code}
<script>
jQuery(document).ready(function() {
jQuery("h1#logo a img,h1#logo a,h1#logo").css("background", "white"); 
});
</script>
{code}

Note: Also {noformat}[.css]("background", "#F6F6F6"){noformat} can be used to apply an HTML color code as the background color when hovering the mouse over the logo.

